issue.title: fix(android): add deselectItem to Androids ListView
issue.body:
On iOS you use `$.lst_open.deselectItem(0, e.itemIndex)` to deselect a clicked item. This method is not needed on Android but also not available in the SDK so you have to add an `if OS_IOS` all the time.

This PR will just add an empty method to the Android ListView so you can remove the `if OS_IOS` statement.

comment.body: For parity with the current iOS implementation, this is the correct way. Changing the default behavior could be inside future versions then. As it was not requested so far, it seems like low prio though.

Enhances cache management and workflow summary reporting

Implements cache cleanup logic to remove old entries from previous executions, ensuring only current session cache is utilized. Introduces methods for clearing the cache and retrieving cache statistics, improving monitoring capabilities. Updates the AutomatedWorkflow to print a summary of processing statistics upon completion, including cache information. Additionally, refines logging for better tracking of cache operations and workflow outcomes.

Enhances GIF settings and cache validation in automated workflow

Updates gif_settings.yaml to allow automatic height calculation for better aspect ratio preservation. Implements cache validation logic in the AutomatedWorkflow to clean up invalid cache entries, improving cache management and ensuring only valid outputs are retained. Adds CLI support for cache validation, providing users with feedback on cache status and cleaned entries. Refines logging for better tracking of cache operations and workflow outcomes.

Enhances GIF segmentation and multiprocessing capabilities

Updates gif_settings.yaml to introduce multiprocessing configuration options, allowing for dynamic analysis of optimal worker counts based on system capabilities. Refines the AutomatedWorkflow and GifGenerator classes to utilize the new multiprocessing settings, improving parallel processing efficiency during GIF segment creation. Implements a method for calculating optimal segmentation workers, enhancing performance based on hardware and system load. Additionally, updates logging to provide detailed feedback on worker utilization and segment processing progress.

Enhances GIF validation and summary generation in automated workflow

Introduces a fast GIF validation method to improve performance during GIF processing, allowing for quicker checks without full frame iteration. Updates the AutomatedWorkflow and VideoSegmenter classes to utilize this new validation method, enhancing efficiency in GIF segment handling. Additionally, implements comprehensive summary generation for segments, providing detailed insights into MP4 and GIF files, including size, duration, and frame count. Refines logging to improve tracking of summary creation and validation processes.

Add crop detection settings to GIF configuration and enhance crop validation logic

Introduces crop detection configuration in gif_settings.yaml, allowing users to enable or disable crop detection and set thresholds for significant cropping. Updates the GifGenerator class to respect these settings, ensuring that crop suggestions are only applied when they exceed defined border thresholds. This enhancement aims to prevent unintended cropping and improve the overall quality of generated GIFs.

Update GIF settings and enhance logging in automated workflow

Increased the maximum file size limit for GIF uploads in gif_settings.yaml from 8MB to 10MB to align with Discord's updated limits for free users. Improved logging in the AutomatedWorkflow class by implementing a safe filename method for better handling of Unicode characters in log messages. Additionally, refined file sorting logic to prioritize files based on creation time, enhancing the efficiency of file processing.
